<em>Vivarium</em>, 37(2): 143&ndash;167.
doi:10.1163/156853400323241913</li>

<li>Freppert, Lucan, 1988, <em>The Basis of Morality According to
William Ockham</em>, Chicago, IL: Franciscan Herald Press.</li>

<li>G&aacute;l, Gedeon, 1982, &ldquo;William of Ockham Died
&lsquo;Impenitent&rsquo; in April 1347&rdquo;, <em>Franciscan
Studies</em>, 42: 90&ndash;95. doi:10.1353/frc.1982.0011</li>

<li>Goddu, Andr&eacute;, 1984, <em>The Physics of William of
Ockham</em> (Studien und Texte zur Geistesgeschichte des Mittelalters
16), Leiden: E.J. Brill.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, &ldquo;Ockham&rsquo;s Philosophy of
Nature&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Spade1999">Spade 1999a</a>:
 143&ndash;167 (ch. 7). doi:10.1017/CCOL052158244X.008</li>

<li>Hagedorn, Eric W., 2022, &ldquo;The Changing Role of Theological
Authority in Ockham&rsquo;s Razor&rdquo;, <em>Res Philosophica</em>,
99(2): 97&ndash;120. doi:10.11612/resphil.2165</li>

<li>Hirvonen, Vesa, 2004, <em>Passions in William Ockham&rsquo;s
Philosophical Psychology</em>, Dordrecht: Kluwer.
doi:10.1007/978-1-4020-2119-0</li>

<li>Karger, Elizabeth Christian, 1976, <em>A Study of William of
Ockham&rsquo;s Modal Logic</em>, Ph.D. dissertation, University of
California, Berkeley.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, &ldquo;Ockham&rsquo;s Misunderstood
Theory of Intuitive and Abstractive Cognition&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Spade1999">Spade 1999a</a>:
 204&ndash;226 (ch. 9). doi:10.1017/CCOL052158244X.010</li>

<li>Keele, Rondo, 2002, <em>Formal Ontology in the Fourteenth Century:
The Chatton Principle and Ockham&rsquo;s Razor,</em> Ph.D.
dissertation, Indiana University, Bloomington.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010, <em>Ockham Explained: From Razor to
Rebellion</em> (Ideas Explained Series 7), Chicago: Open Court.</li>

<li>King, Peter, 1999, &ldquo;Ockham&rsquo;s Ethical Theory&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Spade1999">Spade 1999a</a>:
 227&ndash;244 (ch. 10). doi:10.1017/CCOL052158244X.011</li>

<li>Kilcullen, John, 1999, &ldquo;The Political Writings&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Spade1999">Spade 1999a</a>:
 302&ndash;325 (ch. 13). doi:10.1017/CCOL052158244X.014</li>

<li>Leppin, Volker, 2003, <em>Wilhelm von Ockham: Gelehrter, Streiter,
Bettelm&ouml;nch</em>, Darmstadt: Primus.</li>

<li>Majcherek, Kamil, 2022, &ldquo;Why Is a House Nothing More than
Stones and Pieces of Wood?&rdquo;, <em>Recherches de Th&eacute;ologie
et Philosophie M&eacute;di&eacute;vales</em>, 89(1): 109&ndash;144.
doi:10.2143/RTPM.89.1.3290730</li>

<li>Maurer, Armand A., 1962, <em>Medieval Philosophy</em>
(Gilson&rsquo;s A History of Philosophy), New York: Random House.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1978, &ldquo;Method in Ockham&rsquo;s
Nominalism:&rdquo;, <em>The Monist</em>, 61(3): 426&ndash;443.
doi:10.5840/monist197861334</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1984, &ldquo;Ockham&rsquo;s Razor and
Chatton&rsquo;s Anti-Razor&rdquo;, <em>Mediaeval Studies</em>, 46:
463&ndash;475. doi:10.1484/J.MS.2.306670</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, <em>The Philosophy of William of
Ockham in the Light of Its Principles</em> (Studies and Texts 133),
Toronto: Pontifical Institute of Mediaeval Studies.</li>

<li>McGrade, Arthur Stephen, 1974, <em>The Political Thought of
William of Ockham: Personal and Institutional Principles</em>
(Cambridge Studies in Medieval Life and Thought, third series, 7),
London/New York: Cambridge University Press. Paperback edition, 2002.
doi:10.1017/CBO9780511561238</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, &ldquo;Natural Law and Moral
Omnipotence&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Spade1999">Spade 1999a</a>:
 273&ndash;301 (ch. 12). doi:10.1017/CCOL052158244X.013</li>

<li>Michon, Cyrille, 1994, <em>Nominalisme: la th&eacute;orie de la
signification d&rsquo;Occam</em> (Sic et non), Paris: J. Vrin.</li>

<li>Normore, Calvin G., 1975, <em>The Logic of Time and Modality in
the Later Middle Ages: The Contribution of William of Ockham</em>,
Ph.D. dissertation, University of Toronto.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1998, &ldquo;Picking and Choosing: Anselm
and Ockham on Choice&rdquo;, <em>Vivarium</em>, 36(1): 23&ndash;39.
doi:10.1163/1568534982579378</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, &ldquo;Some Aspects of Ockham&rsquo;s
Logic&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Spade1999">Spade 1999a</a>:
 31&ndash;52 (ch. 2). doi:10.1017/CCOL052158244X.003</li>

<li>Panaccio, Claude, 1990, &ldquo;Connotative Terms in Ockham&rsquo;s
Mental Language&rdquo;, <em>Cahiers
d&rsquo;&eacute;pist&eacute;mologie</em>, no. 9016. Montr&eacute;al:
Universit&eacute; du Qu&eacute;bec &agrave; Montr&eacute;al.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1991, <em>Les Mots, les Concepts et les
Choses. Le s&eacute;mantique de Guillaume d&rsquo;Occam et le
nominalisme d&rsquo;aujourd&rsquo;hui</em>, Montr&eacute;al-Paris:
Bellarmin-Vrin.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, <em>Le Discours Int&eacute;rieur: de
Platon &agrave; Guillaume d&rsquo;Ockham</em>, Paris: &Eacute;ditions
du Seuil.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2004. <em>Ockham on Concepts</em>,
Aldershot, England: Ashgate.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2012, &ldquo;Intellections and Volitions in
Ockham&rsquo;s Nominalism&rdquo;, in <em>Emotion and Cognitive Life in
Medieval and Early Modern Philosophy</em>, Martin Pickav&eacute; and
Lisa Shapiro (eds.), Oxford: Oxford University Press, 75&ndash;93.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199579914.003.0005</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2014, &ldquo;Ockham: Intuition and
Knowledge&rdquo;, in <em>Rational Intuition: Philosophical Roots,
Scientific Investigations</em>, Lisa M. Osbeck and Barbara S. Held
(eds.), New York: Cambridge University Press, 55&ndash;74.
doi:10.1017/CBO9781139136419.004</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;Ockham&rsquo;s
Externalism&rdquo;, in <em>Intentionality, Cognition, and Mental
Representation in Medieval Philosophy</em>, Gyula Klima (ed.), New
York: Fordham University Press, 166&ndash;185.
doi:10.5422/fordham/9780823262748.003.0008</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016, &ldquo;Ockham on Nominal Definitions,
Synonymy and Mental Language&rdquo;, in <em>Formal Approaches and
Natural Language in Medieval Logic</em> (Textes et &eacute;tudes du
moyen &acirc;ge 82), Laurent Cesalli, Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Goubier,
and Alain De Libera (eds.), Barcelona: F&eacute;d&eacute;ration
internationale des instituts d&rsquo;&eacute;tudes
m&eacute;di&eacute;vales, 393&ndash;415.
doi:10.1484/M.TEMA-EB.4.2017105</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2023, <em>Ockham&rsquo;s Nominalism: A
Philosophical Introduction</em>, New York: Oxford University Press.
doi:10.1093/oso/9780190078980.001.0001</li>

<li>Panaccio, Claude and David Pich&eacute;, 2010,
&ldquo;Ockham&rsquo;s Reliabilism and the Intuition of
Non-Existents&rdquo;, in <em>Rethinking the History of Skepticism: The
Missing Medieval Background</em> (Studien und Texte zur
Geistesgeschichte des Mittelalters 103), Henrik Lagerlund (ed.),
Leiden/Boston: Brill, 97&ndash;118.
doi:10.1163/ej.9789004170612.i-238.33</li>

<li>Pelletier, Jenny E., 2013, <em>William Ockham on Metaphysics: The
Science of Being and God</em> (Studien und Texte zur Geistesgeschichte
des Mittelalters 109), Leiden/Boston: Brill.
doi:10.1163/9789004230163</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2022, &ldquo;Getting Real: Ockham on the
Human Contribution to the Nature and Production of Artifacts&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophies</em>, 7(5): article 90.
doi:10.3390/philosophies7050090</li>

<li>Robinson, Jonathan, 2013, <em>William of Ockham&rsquo;s Early
Theory of Property Rights in Context</em> (Studies in Medieval and
Reformation Traditions 166), Leiden/Boston: Brill.
doi:10.1163/9789004245730</li>

<li>Schierbaum, Sonja, 2014, <em>Ockham&rsquo;s Assumption of Mental
Speech: Thinking in a World of Particulars</em> (Investigating
Medieval Philosophy 6), Boston: Brill. doi:10.1163/9789004277625</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017, &ldquo;Intellections and Volitions:
Ockham&rsquo;s Voluntarism Reconsidered&rdquo;, in <em>The Language of
Thought in Late Medieval Philosophy: Essays in Honor of Claude
Panaccio</em> (Historical-Analytical Studies on Nature, Mind and
