doi:10.1017/S0012217300012075</li>

<li>Wood, Rega, 1999, &ldquo;Ockham&rsquo;s Repudiation of
Pelagianism&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Spade1999">Spade 1999a</a>:
 350&ndash;374 (ch. 15). doi:10.1017/CCOL052158244X.016</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="OtheBibl">Other Bibliographies</h3>

<p>
Ample bibliographies of the secondary literature up to 1990 may be
found in:</p>

<ul class="hanging">

<li>Beckmann, Jan P., 1992, <em>Ockham&mdash;Bibliographie:
1900&ndash;1990</em>, Hamburg: Felix Meiner.</li>

<li>Heynick, Valens, 1950, &ldquo;Ockham-Literatur: 1919-1949&rdquo;,
<em>Franziskanische Studien</em>, 32: 164&ndash;83.</li>

<li>Reilly, James P., 1968, &ldquo;Ockham Bibliography:
1950&ndash;1967&rdquo;, <em>Franciscan Studies</em>, 28:
197&ndash;214.</li>
</ul>

<div id="other-internet-resources">

<h2 id="Oth">Other Internet Resources</h2>

<ul>

 <li><a href="https://pvspade.com/Logic" target="other"><em>Mediaeval Logic and Philosophy</em></a>,
 maintained by Paul Vincent Spade (Indiana University). Includes links
and on-line texts relevant to Ockham such as:

<ul>

 <li><a href="https://pvspade.com/Logic/docs/thoughts1_1a.pdf" target="other"><em>Thoughts, Words and Things: An Introduction to Late Mediaeval Logic and Semantic Theory</em></a>,
 by Paul Vincent Spade (Indiana University) [Version 1.1a, in PDF].

<p class="bibnote">
(Contains much on Ockham&rsquo;s logic and semantics.)</p> </li>

<li>Translation of William of Ockham,
 <a href="https://pvspade.com/Logic/docs/circavirtutes.htm" target="other"><em>Concerning Virtues and Vices</em></a>,
 by Rondo Keele.

<p class="bibnote">
(This is Keele&rsquo;s translation of Ockham&rsquo;s short ethical
treatise <em>Circa virtutes et vitia</em>.)</p> </li>
</ul> </li>

<li  id="Oth-kilcullen"><a href="https://publications.thebritishacademy.ac.uk/pubs/dialogus/ockdial.html" target="other"><em>Dialogus</em></a>,
 Latin Text and English Translation, John Kilcullen, et al.
(ed./trans.), sponsored by the British Academy.

<p class="bibnote">
(Includes extremely helpful materials such as a detailed summary in
English of most of the <em>Dialogue</em>.)</p> </li>
</ul>
</div>

